{{- define "worktree-rules" -}}
{{- if eq .RoleType "reviewer"}}

WORKTREE GIT RULES:
- All git commands MUST use -C {{.Worktree}} to prevent shared state corruption.
{{- else}}

WORKTREE RULES:
- All git commands MUST use -C {{.Worktree}} to prevent shared state corruption.
- File Read/Edit paths must match exactly — the edit tool tracks reads by string, not inode.
  Use {{.Worktree}}/path for ALL file operations. Never retype or reconstruct the path.
- To CREATE new files: use Write directly without Read. Do not attempt Read first (it will error).
{{- end}}
{{- end -}}
